<a name="summary-8" class="anchor" href="#summary-8"></a>Summary</h1>
<p>In this story we analyzed three different security vulnerabilities in Codoforum, a popular board software. Each of these issues could lead to a complete takeover of the application. Weâ€™ve learned that a malicious user can take multiple paths when attacking an application and that finding only one single vulnerability is enough to fully compromise its security. Hence it is our task to make our applications as robust and secure as possible. Checking all user inputs properly and leveraging existing and proven sanitization and validation mechanisms is the first step towards a solid defense.<br>
Due to the severity of the issues weâ€™ve postponed the release of our story since the release of a fix in March. If you are hosting a Codoforum and didnâ€™t update your installation yet, we highly recommend to do so now. Thanks to the Codoforum team, a patch version was quickly released after our reports.</p>
